# AI Linux Assistant — grant the ACTIVE logged-in user access to /dev/uinput (for ydotool input
# injection) WITHOUT putting them in the `input` group. The `uaccess` tag makes systemd-logind add a
# per-session ACL, so only the currently-logged-in user gets access — and it grants uinput (input
# *injection*) only, NOT read access to /dev/input/event* (which would allow system-wide keylogging
# and defeat Wayland's input isolation). Installed by `./ai-linux setup` to /etc/udev/rules.d/.
KERNEL=="uinput", TAG+="uaccess", OPTIONS+="static_node=uinput"
